


VORT2PCX(1)              USER COMMANDS                VORT2PCX(1)



NAME
     vort2pcx  -  converts  a  VORT   colour   mapped   file   to
     Microsoft/ZSoft PCX format.

SYNOPSIS
     vort2pcx file1 file2

DESCRIPTION
     Vort2pcx reads in  a  colour  mapped  VORT  image  file  and
     creates a PCX format image file. The PCX file format created
     is:
               .8 bits per pixel
               .1 image plane
               .colour mapped
               .run-length encoded

     Windows 3.0 Paint can handle such a format.

BUGS
     Doesn't handle the general VORT image case (i.e. only colour
     mapped VORT images).

     The file produced may not have the most appropriate PCX for-
     mat for the VORT image (e.g. 16 colour VORT image is written
     as 256 colour PCX image).


SEE ALSO
